@startuml commit-group-overview
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ArrowColor #555555

title dev-workgraph — **commit-group** (§4, §7)\nWork sessions: deterministic grouping + 2 LLM sessions (**commitModel**)

legend top left
  |= Tag |= Meaning |
  | **(D)** | Deterministic — evidence / pure code |
  | **(M:c)** | Ollama **commitModel** (same slot as summarize) |
  | **evidence** | Does **not** run here — only its data inside commit .json |
endlegend

rectangle "**Upstream (not invoked)**" #ECEFF1 {
  card "**evidence**\n.patches on disk" as EVID #CCCCCC
  note bottom of EVID
    commit-group never reads .patch files
    and never calls evidence
  end note
}

rectangle "**Required input**" #E3F2FD {
  card "from **evidence** (D)\ncommits/<ts>/<hash>.json\ndeterministic" as DET
  card "from **summarize** (M:c)\n**summaries/<ts>/<hash>.json**\ncanonical only" as CM
}

rectangle "**commit-group**" #FFF3E0 {
  card "(D) group membership\n+ aggregate deterministic\n+ partition tiers" as DSTEP
  card "(M:c) session 1 classify\nsignals + questions + context bullets" as C1
  card "(M:c) session 2 compose\nfirst-person history" as C2
  card "groups/<timestampEnd>.json" as GOUT
}

rectangle "**summarize**" #FFF8E1 {
  card "canonical summary per commit\n(empty → **(none)** skipped)" as SUM
}

SUM --> CM : **feeds commit-group**
DET --> DSTEP : aggregated from members
CM --> DSTEP : **tierOf** per commit\n+ **exclude empty summaries**
CM --> C1 : member summaries,\nsignals, questionsAnalysis
CM --> C2 : per-tier summaries\nto merge into history
DSTEP --> C1
C1 --> C2
C2 --> GOUT

EVID .. DET : wrote earlier\n(not read directly)

@enduml


@startuml commit-group-summarize-link
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false

title **commit-group** and **summarize** — what is reused vs recalculated

package "**summarize output (per commit)**" #FFF8E1 {
  component "model.summary" as S
  component "model signals\n(technical / architecture / security)" as SIG
  component "model.signalReasons" as SR
  component "model.questionsAnalysis" as Q
  component "model.changeTypes" as CT
}

package "**commit-group reads (no .patch, no evidence cmd)**" #E3F2FD {
  component "commits/<ts>/<hash>.json\n.deterministic (evidence)" as DET
  component "summaries/<ts>/<hash>.json\n.canonical model only" as READ
}

package "**commit-group (D) — always recomputed on run**" #E8F5E9 {
  component "filter **isEmptyCommitSummary**" as FILT
  component "groupByGap membership" as MEM
  component "aggregateDeterministic" as AGG
  component "groups.tiers via tierOf(model)" as TIER
}

package "**commit-group (M:c) — session-level rebuild**" #FFF3E0 {
  component "Session signals re-evaluated\n(at least max of members)" as GSIG
  component "Session questions synthesized\n(merge, dedupe, reframe)" as GQ
  component "hiContext / mediumContext / lowContext" as CTX
  component "history — merge of commit summaries" as HIST
}

S --> READ
SIG --> READ
Q --> READ

READ --> FILT
FILT --> MEM
FILT --> TIER
FILT --> GSIG
FILT --> GQ
DET --> AGG
SIG --> TIER

note bottom of FILT
  Skip commits where provenance.model = **(none)**
  or summary is blank.
  Console: N commits → M for grouping
  (K empty summaries skipped)
end note

note bottom of TIER
  **tierOf** uses summarize signals only:
  hi = any high · medium = any medium, none high
  low = all low OR model is null
end note

note bottom of GQ
  Classify session **rebuilds** session questions from
  member commit questions + session context — not a
  simple string concat; role-aware via project context.
end note

note bottom of GSIG
  On re-run after new commits summarized:
  tiers, session signals, questions, history all
  recomputed from current commit.model values.
end note

@enduml


@startuml commit-group-command
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #888888
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFF3E0

title **commit-group** — Full command flow

start

:loadCommitRecords(commits/ + summaries/);\njoin evidence + canonical summary;

if (No commits?) then (yes)
  #Pink:Run **evidence** first;
  stop
else (no)
endif

:Filter **isEmptyCommitSummary**;
note right: skip (none) / blank summary

:Resolve **groupThresholdDays** + **groupMaxCommits**\n(prompt or --days / --max-commits);

:groupByGap(commits, days, max)\n**oldest first**;

:Pick **commitModel** (same slot as summarize);

:loadProjectContext -> classify + compose system prompts;

partition "Per work session (oldest group first)" {
  :buildGroupRecord(members) **(D)**;
  note right
    groups.commits[] ordered hashes
    groups.tiers = partitionTiers(members)
    deterministic = aggregateDeterministic(members)
    model = null (until LLM)
  end note

  if (group file exists with model?) then (yes)
    :Skip LLM (append-only);
  else (no)
    partition "**Session 1 — classify (M:c)**" {
      :Input: aggregated deterministic,\ntier-annotated members (summary + signals\n+ per-commit questions as context),\ngroups.tiers reference;
      :Output: session **signals** + signalReasons,\n**questions[]**, changeTypes, confidence,\nhiContext / mediumContext / lowContext;
      :enforceSignalReasons;
    }

    partition "**Session 2 — compose (M:c)**" {
      :Input: classify result +\nper-commit summaries by tier;
      :Output: **history** only\n(first-person merge);
    }

    :technologies = mergeTechnologies(members)\n**(D)** union of commit models;
    :Write groups/<timestampEnd>.json;
  endif
}

#LightGreen:Done;

floating note left
  On model failure: save group with model=null\n(deterministic + tiers kept) for retry.
  **Append-only:** skips groups that already have model.
  New commits → **extension groups** only (§4).
  To rebuild: delete group files manually.
end note

stop

@enduml


@startuml commit-group-deterministic
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #888888
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #E8F5E9

title **commit-group** — Deterministic steps (D)\nNo evidence command · uses commit .json from disk

start

:Load evidence from commits/**/*.json;\njoin **summaries/<ts>/<hash>.json** (canonical);

note right
  Each joined record:
  • deterministic (from evidence)
  • model (from summarize, may be empty)
  **.partN.json / .merge.json not loaded**
end note

:Filter out **isEmptyCommitSummary**;

partition "1. Group membership — groupByGap" {
  :Walk chronologically;
  if (gap > groupThresholdDays\nOR group size >= groupMaxCommits?) then (yes)
    :Close group, start new;
  else (no)
    :Same session;
  endif
  note right: Single-commit groups are valid
}

partition "2. groups.commits (D)" {
  :Ordered list of member hashes;
}

partition "3. groups.tiers — partitionTiers (D)" {
  :For each member: **tierOf(commit)**;
  note right
    Uses **summarize** signals only:
    hi / medium / low
    model null -> low tier
  end note
  :Every hash in exactly one tier bucket;
}

partition "4. aggregateDeterministic (D)" {
  :Union changedFiles per status;
  :Sum linesAdded / linesDeleted;
  :Union folders, areas, excludedFiles;
  note right
    Same rules as evidence, merged across members.
    **Does not** re-read Git or patches.
  end note
}

:Write deterministic layer to group JSON\nbefore any LLM call;

stop

@enduml


@startuml commit-group-model-layer
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam classBackgroundColor #FAFAFA

title **GroupModelLayer** — two LLM sessions (M:c)

class "GroupRecord" as GR {
  groupId, timestampStart, timestampEnd, commitCount
  groups { commits[], tiers { low, medium, hi } }
  deterministic : DeterministicLayer **(D)**
  model : GroupModelLayer | null
}

class "Session 1 — classify" as C1 #FFF3E0 {
  **Rebuilt session signals**
  technicalSignal / architectureSignal / securitySignal
  signalReasons (patch-grounded, session scope)
  --
  **questions[]** — session-level
  synthesized from member gaps
  (not simple concat of commit questions)
  --
  changeTypes[], confidence
  hiContext[] / mediumContext[] / lowContext[]
  (meaning-merged bullets, not commit hashes)
}

class "Session 2 — compose" as C2 #FFF3E0 {
  **history** : string
  First-person merge of commit summaries
  HIGH = full detail · MEDIUM = brief
  LOW = optional mention
}

class "CLI (D post)" as CLI #E3F2FD {
  technologies[] = mergeTechnologies(members)
  provenance { model, generatedAt }
}

GR *-- C1
C1 --> C2 : classify feeds compose
C2 --> CLI
CLI --> GR

note right of C1
  Input from **summarize**:
  per-commit summary, signals, questions
  + deterministic tiers reference
end note

note bottom of GR
  **evidence** does not participate in model steps.
  Member **patches never loaded**.
end note

@enduml


